## Why This Is Asked

Tests batch ingestion, per-record contracts, idempotent upserts, and basic governance. It also requires handling invalid rows and a simple redaction policy.

## Key Concepts

- Batch ingestion and CSV parsing
- Per-record contracts and validation
- MERGE upsert into Iceberg
- Bad data routing
- Simple role-based redaction policy and audit

## Code Example

```javascript
// Pseudo-implementation sketch
function validate(row) {
  if (!row.supplier_id || !row.region || !row.order_id || !row.order_ts) return false;
  if (row.total_amount == null || row.total_amount < 0) return false;
  return true;
}

function processBatch(csvFiles) {
  const goodRows = [];
  const badRows = [];

  csvFiles.forEach(file => {
    const rows = parseCSV(file);
    rows.forEach(row => {
      if (validate(row)) {
        goodRows.push(row);
      } else {
        badRows.push({...row, error: 'Validation failed', timestamp: new Date()});
      }
    });
  });

  // Write bad data
  writeToPath(badRows, 'bad_data/');

  // Upsert good data
  executeMerge(goodRows, 'target_table', ['region', 'order_id']);
}

function redactForRole(data, userRole) {
  if (userRole !== 'admin') {
    return data.map(row => ({...row, total_amount: 'REDACTED'}));
  }
  return data;
}
```

## Validation Strategy

- Schema validation: required fields, data types, constraints
- Business rules: total_amount >= 0, valid timestamps
- Data quality: duplicate detection, reference integrity

